import numpy
import glob
import matplotlib.pyplot

filnames= sorted(glob.glob('C:\\Users\DELL\Desktop\swc-python\data\inflammation*.csv'))
print(filnames)
filename = filnames[0:3]
for file in filename:
    print(file)
    data = numpy.loadtxt(fname=file, delimiter = ',')
    print(data)
    
    fig= matplotlib.pyplot.figure(figsize=(10,3))

    axes1= fig.add_subplot(1,3,1)
    axes2= fig.add_subplot(1,3,2)
    axes3= fig.add_subplot(1,3,3)

    axes1.set_ylabel('average')
    axes1.plot(numpy.mean(data, axis=0))
    axes2.set_ylabel('max')
    axes2.plot(numpy.max(data, axis=0))
    axes3.set_ylabel('min')
    axes3.plot(numpy.min(data, axis=0))

import numpy
import glob
import matplotlib.pyplot

filnames= sorted(glob.glob('C:\\Users\DELL\Desktop\swc-python\data\inflammation*.csv'))
print(filnames)
filename = filnames[0:3]
for file in filename:
    print(file)
    data = numpy.loadtxt(fname=file, delimiter = ',')
    print(data)
    
    fig= matplotlib.pyplot.figure(figsize=(10,3))

    axes1= fig.add_subplot(1,3,1)
    axes2= fig.add_subplot(1,3,2)
    axes3= fig.add_subplot(1,3,3)

    axes1.set_ylabel('average')
    axes1.plot(numpy.mean(data, axis=1))
    axes2.set_ylabel('max')
    axes2.plot(numpy.max(data, axis=1))
    axes3.set_ylabel('min')
    axes3.plot(numpy.min(data, axis=1))

import numpy
import glob
import matplotlib.pyplot

filnames= sorted(glob.glob('C:\\Users\DELL\Desktop\swc-python\data\inflammation*.csv'))
print(filnames)
filename = filnames[0:3]
for file in filename:
    print(file)
    data = numpy.loadtxt(fname=file, delimiter = ',')
    print(data)
    max_inflammation_0 = numpy.max(data, axis=0)[0]
    max_inflammation_20 = numpy.max(data, axis=0)[20]

    if max_inflammation_0 == 0 and max_inflammation_20 == 20:
    
        print('Something is wrong with inflammation data')
    elif numpy.sum(numpy.min(data, axis=0)) == 0:
        print('More than one thing is wrong with data')
    else:
        print('data is fine you can procead')

import numpy
import glob
import matplotlib.pyplot

filnames= sorted(glob.glob('C:\\Users\DELL\Desktop\swc-python\data\inflammation*.csv'))
print(filnames)
for file in filnames:
    print(file)
    data = numpy.loadtxt(fname=file, delimiter = ',')
    print(data)
    max_inflammation_0 = numpy.max(data, axis=0)[0]
    max_inflammation_20 = numpy.max(data, axis=0)[20]

    if max_inflammation_0 == 0 and max_inflammation_20 == 20:
    
        print('Something is wrong with inflammation data')
    elif numpy.sum(numpy.min(data, axis=0)) == 0:
        print('More than one thing is wrong with data')
    else:
        print('data is fine you can procead')

import math
def Resonance_frequency(spring_constant, mass):
    number = spring_constant/mass
    return math.sqrt(number)*(1/(2*3.14))

    data = numpy.loadtxt(fname=filename, delimiter = ',')
  
    
    fig= matplotlib.pyplot.figure(figsize=(10,3))

    axes1= fig.add_subplot(1,3,1)
    axes2= fig.add_subplot(1,3,2)
    axes3= fig.add_subplot(1,3,3)

    axes1.set_ylabel('average')
    axes1.plot(numpy.mean(data, axis=0))
    axes2.set_ylabel('max')
    axes2.plot(numpy.max(data, axis=0))
    axes3.set_ylabel('min')
    axes3.plot(numpy.min(data, axis=0))

    max_inflammation_20 = numpy.max(data, axis=0)[20]

    if max_inflammation_0 == 0 and max_inflammation_20 == 20:
    
        print('Something is wrong with inflammation data')
    elif numpy.sum(numpy.min(data, axis=0)) == 0:
        print('More than one thing is wrong with data')
    else:
        print('data is fine you can procead')

    return (data - numpy.mean(data)) + target_mean_value

In [146]:
highest = 0
def greatest(num1,num2,num3):
    if (num1 > num2) and (num1 > num3):
        highest = num1
    elif (num2 > num1) and (num2 > num3):
         highest = num2
    else:
         highest = num3
    return highest


print(greatest(2,3,5))

5

    assert greatest(-1,-5,-7) == -1
    print(greatest(-1,-5,-7))
    assert greatest(0,-9,-10) == 0
    print(greatest(0,-9,-10))

In [129]:
def range_overlap(values):
    """Return common overlap among a set of [left, right] ranges."""
    max_left = 0.0
    min_right = 1.0
    for (left, right) in values:
        max_left = max(max_left, left)
        min_right = min(min_right, right)
        return (max_left, min_right)

def test_range_overlap():
    assert range_overlap([ (0.0, 1.0), (5.0, 6.0) ]) == None
    assert range_overlap([ (0.0, 1.0), (1.0, 2.0) ]) == None
    assert range_overlap([ (0.0, 1.0) ]) == (0.0, 1.0)
    assert range_overlap([ (2.0, 3.0), (2.0, 4.0) ]) == (2.0, 3.0)
    assert range_overlap([ (0.0, 1.0), (0.0, 2.0), (-1.0, 1.0) ]) == (0.0, 1.0)
    assert range_overlap([]) == None
